news.title: Godrej Properties plans Rs 7,500 crore investment in next 12-18 months
news.para: "We will invest USD 1 billion (around Rs 7,500 crore) over the next 12-18 months on development of new projects," Godrej Executive Chairman Pirojsha Godrej said, adding that the planned investments would be in mix of equity and debt.

news.title: Vadodara civic body claims its coffers have got richer due to building permissions
news.para: It has come to light that in 2018-19 VMC received Rs 188.48crore towards charges for building construction permissions. In 2019-20, the amount was Rs 192.96 crore and Rs 179.77crore in 2020-21.

news.title: Gurugram: Brisk Lumbini residents file complaint about poor construction quality
news.para: In their complaint, the residents alleged they had earlier raised concern about plaster chunks falling from balconies, cracks in pillars and seepage in the basement but no attention had been paid to it.

news.title: Rajasthan budget may not allocate funds for Jaipur Metro phase-II
news.para: Many believe, the government should consider Metro on Tonk Road as corridor which runs from South to North and connects all major areas.

news.title: Navi Mumbai Metro just a nod away from March-end start
news.para: The railway board on Friday approved the rolling stock, that is, coaches and operational equipment, of the Navi Mumbai Metro following a two-day inspection by the commissioner of metro railway safety (CMRS) on January 17- 18.

news.title: Hyderabad: Badangpet, Shankarpally hub of illegal structures
news.para: Officials found that a majority of the unauthorised constructions were taking place across Badangpet Municipal Corporation, Shankarpally, Pochampally and Dundigal municipalities.

news.title: Over 290 buildings without BU nod sealed: Ahmedabad civic body to Gujarat HC
news.para: The Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation has informed the Gujarat high court on Saturday that, since March 2021, it has sealed 297 buildings and 3,559 units that do not have valid Building Use permission.

news.title: Nashik civic body eyes Rs 40 crore additional revenue annually via property tax
news.para: The NMC had found 4.5 lakh properties in the city during the survey of all the properties through a private agency around three years back.

news.title: Delhi: Residents of Bawana fear for lives, say over dozens more buildings on verge of collapse
news.para: On Friday afternoon, a portion of an old building built under Rajiv Gandhi Awas Yojana in Bawana's JJ colony collapsed. According to the police, the three-storey building was in a dilapidated condition.

news.title: Nagpur: HC rejects Sitabuldi shopkeeper's plea against Glocal Mall
news.para: While hearing a plea by Samrat Garment through partner Prasanna Modi alleging violations by builder Goel Ganga Infrastructure and inaction by Nagpur Improvement Trust (NIT), a division bench comprising justices Sunil Shukre and Anil Pansare found no merit in the petition.

news.title: Debris tumbles down amid rescue efforts in Chintels Paradiso building; residents panic
news.para: The police have lodged an FIR at Bajghera police station against the managing director of realty firm Chintels India on charges of causing death due to negligence, Gurugram Deputy Commissioner of Police Deepak Saharan said.

news.title: Sushma group raises Rs 100 crore from Motilal Oswal
news.para: The fund will also be used to give exit to existing lender LIC housing and remaining will be used to complete the construction of project.

news.title: Germany and Austria told to curb boom in home prices
news.para: "Austria and Germany...had already received ESRB warnings in 2016 and 2019, respectively (but their) vulnerabilities have not been addressed sufficiently," the ESRB said.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Income tax department finds Rs 7 crore cash, gold in searches on builders
news.para: The raids started on Thursday on Shilp, Shivalik and Sharda Developers by teams comprising 50 officers and 100 staff members from across Gujarat.

news.title: No increase in property tax in North Delhi civic body's budget
news.para: There was also no increase in property tax. Goswami accepted that in the last decade South MCD has not paid rent worth Rs 2,833 crores to North MCD but failed to explain why it happened.
